## 📌 Overview
This project demonstrates a CI/CD pipeline that automatically deploys a website to an Azure Linux Virtual Machine using GitHub Actions.

## ⚙️ Tools Used
- Microsoft Azure (Linux VM)
- Nginx (Web Server)
- Git & GitHub
- GitHub Actions
- SSH

## 🏗 Architecture

[ Local Machine ]
        ↓
[ GitHub Repository ]
        ↓
[ GitHub Actions (CI/CD Pipeline) ]
        ↓
[ Azure Linux VM ]
        ↓
[ Nginx Web Server ]
        ↓
[ Live Website ]

## 🚀 What This Does
- Automatically deploys website updates on every push to the main branch  
- Uses SSH to securely connect to the server  
- Restarts Nginx after deployment  

## 🧪 How It Works
1. Code is pushed to GitHub  
2. GitHub Actions workflow is triggered  
3. Files are copied to the Azure VM  
4. Nginx serves the updated website  

## 📸 Result
After updating the HTML file and pushing changes, the live website updates automatically without manual intervention.

## 🔧 Challenges Faced
